Chaz Dean is In My Chair! (Link in Bio)
We cover a LOT. From his humble beginnings to creating the 3rd largest haircare  brand in 🇺🇸, to a devastating lawsuit and being on reality TV Bravo’s Flipping Out. Chaz trusts his gut and treats everyone with kindness. I had a great time chatting with him. 
#ChazDean
#QVC

AVA PHILLIPPE X CHANEL 💄 ❤️💄❤️💄❤️
@avaphillippe @welovecoco 

First I applied Ultra Le Tint B30 with a wet sponge to give flawless coverage. 

I used the Les Beiges 390 Soleil Tan Bronze Bronzing gel along the edges of the face to add “invisible” and soft definition and give a warm glow. 

I set the makeup with Poudre Universelle Libre using a brush and then again with the Chanel powder puff in the T-Zone. It’s 95 degrees today! The Puff really works the power into the skin for more mattifying. 

I filled in her brows with Defining Brow Pencil Blonde Dore 804 giving her natural arch a little more depth. 

For the eyes I used all four shades of the New Les 4 ombres Byzance in 318 Parure Venitienne. 
I used the brown shade on the crease of the eye to create definition. 
I mixed the two top shades: a gold and peach and applied it to the center and the entire lid. 
I used the bottom right frosty blue shadow on the inner corners of the eye to open the eyes. 
Next I used Stilo Waterproof Eye Pencil in Noir on the lash line and flicked out the corners for a cat eye. 

Lastly I used Le Volume Mascara in Noir on the top and bottom lashes. 

For the blush I mixed Joues Contraste in 80 jersey and 320 Rouge Profond. Applied to the apple of the cheeks and towards the ears

I used Baumé Essential in Rosee on the top of the cheek bones and bridge of the nose. 

For the lip I applied  Rouge Coco Ultra Hydrating Lip Color in 444 Gabrielle

Lastly I misted the entire face using
HYDRA BEAUTY ESSENCE MIST
TO LOCK IN THE MAKEUP AND SET THE MATTIFYING UNIVERSALLE POWDER AS IT IS SUCH A HOT DAY.
